e Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, and he said, \"Keep reciting, O you,\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Faith \u0627\u0644\u0627\u064a\u0645\u0627\u0646&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Faith \u0627\u0644\u0627\u064a\u0645\u0627\u0646","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/faith-iman\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":14036,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2013\/05\/07\/ibn-masud-quran-old-treasures\/","url_meta":{"origin":3987,"position":2},"title":"Ibn Mas\u2019ud on Quran: Middle chapters are my old treasures","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"May 7, 2013","format":false,"excerpt":"Ibn Yazid reported: Ibn Mas\u2019ud, may Allah be pleased with him, said about Surat Bani Isra'il, Al-Kahf, Maryam, Ta Ha, and Al-Anbiya', \"They were among the first chapters I learned and they are my old treasures.\" Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 al-Bukha\u0304ri\u0304 4431 Grade: Sahih (authentic) according to Al-Bukhari \u0639\u0646 \u0627\u0628\u0646 \u064a\u0632\u064a\u062f \u0628\u0652\u0646\u0650\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Quran Exegesis \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0641\u0633\u064a\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Quran Exegesis \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0641\u0633\u064a\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/quran-exegesis-tafsir\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":35124,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2021\/02\/01\/allah-gives-no-weight\/","url_meta":{"origin":3987,"position":3},"title":"Hadith on Fame: Allah gives no weight to worldly status","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"February 1, 2021","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Huraira reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cVerily, a prominent and obese man will be brought on the Day of Resurrection who does not weigh as much as a gnat's wing to Allah. Recite the verse: Thus, We will not give them any\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Quran Exegesis \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0641\u0633\u064a\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Quran Exegesis \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0641\u0633\u064a\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/quran-exegesis-tafsir\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":31792,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2019\/06\/03\/shield-fire-dhikr-allah\/","url_meta":{"origin":3987,"position":4},"title":"Hadith on Dhikr: Your shield from Hellfire is remembrance of Allah","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"June 3, 2019","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Huraira reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cTake up your shields.\u201d They said, \u201cO Messenger of Allah, is the enemy present?\u201d The Prophet said, \u201cNo, rather your shields from the Hellfire are to declare the glory of Allah, the praise of Allah, there\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Quran Exegesis \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0641\u0633\u064a\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Quran Exegesis \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0641\u0633\u064a\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/quran-exegesis-tafsir\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":11501,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2013\/01\/18\/division-sahabah-surah-juz\/","url_meta":{"origin":3987,"position":5},"title":"Hadith on Quran: How companions divided the Quran","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"January 18, 2013","format":false,"excerpt":"Aws ibn Hudhayfah reported: I asked the companions of the Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, how they divided the Quran. They said, \u201cThree chapters, then five, then seven, then nine, then eleven, then thirteen, and then al-Mufassal as a single part.\u201d Source: Sunan Abi\u0304 Da\u0304wu\u0304d 1393\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quo